w moderate $p_{\\rm T}$ dependence in mid-central collisions. This might be\nan indication of possible viscous corrections to the equilibrium distribution\nat hadronic freeze-out, which might help to understand the possible\ncontribution of bulk viscosity in the hadronic phase of the system. Together\nwith existing measurements of individual flow harmonics, the presented results\nprovide further constraints on the initial conditions and the transport\nproperties of the system produced in heavy-ion collisions.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 4 Sep 2017 19:28:17 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 3 Feb 2019 11:05:53 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-02-05"}
