rted in the core\nand propagated outward. The CME structures continued to form during expansion,\nwhich did not become self-similar up to $25 R_\\odot$. The aerodynamic drag was\ninsignificant. The core formed until $4 R_\\odot$. Some of its components were\nobserved to straighten and stretch forward, indicating the transformation of\ntangled structures of the core into a simpler flux rope, which grew and filled\nthe cavity as the CME expanded.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 5 Sep 2017 03:44:53 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-11-04"}
