urements of the decameter sky noise level at\nmidlatitude decameter radars can be used to study the ionospheric absorption of\nhigh-frequency waves in the lower ionosphere during x-ray solar flares. This\ncan be explained by the assumption that the most part of decameter sky noise\ndetected by the radars can be interpreted as produced by ground sources at\ndistances of the first propagation hop (\\textasciitilde{} 3000 km).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 5 Sep 2017 07:00:17 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-04-10"}
